data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each issue and its fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — expression tree no longer compiles

The setters parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression-tree code won't compile. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type columns — naming changes (two issues)

**a) Same-named properties are now uniquified.** If `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` both have `Street`, EF 10 auto-appends a number (e.g. `Street1`). To keep the old shared-column behavior, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; it now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual executed SQL
}
```

Update all other methods on the interface similarly (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
